  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> tortiglioni</strong>&nbsp;to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, then cook&nbsp;for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the<strong> tortiglioni</strong>, reserving 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-pasta-al-forno/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the&nbsp;<strong>smoked streaky bacon </strong>finely<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong>&nbsp;chopped bacon</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-pasta-al-forno/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong>&nbsp;<strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong><br /><br />Once the <strong>bacon</strong> is crisp, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until the <strong>onion</strong> has softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-pasta-al-forno/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>cheddar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> with <span class=\"text-highlight\">the&nbsp;<strong>chopped garlic, dried oregano,&nbsp;</strong></span><span class=\"text-highlight\">half the</span><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong> grated cheese&nbsp;</strong>and a </span>generous pinch of<strong> black pepper </strong>&ndash;<strong>&nbsp;</strong>this is your<strong> cheesy crumb</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-pasta-al-forno/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>onion</strong> has softened, stir through the <strong>cooked tortiglioni,</strong>&nbsp;<strong>cr&egrave;me<span class=\"text-highlight\"> fra&icirc;che</span></strong>, <strong>remaining&nbsp;grated cheese</strong> and reserved <strong>starchy pasta water<br /></strong><br />Season with a generous pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 1 min or until the <strong>cheese</strong> has melted</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-pasta-al-forno/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the<strong> bacon &amp; cheese pasta</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (or use 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> individual dishes!) then top with the <strong>cheesy crumb&nbsp;</strong>and put the dish in the oven for 15 min or until it's golden</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-pasta-al-forno/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>baby plum tomatoes</strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Combine the<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a large bowl</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> lamb's lettuce</strong> and <strong>chopped baby plum tomatoes</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\r\n<p>Tip: don't dress your salad until serving or it will go limp!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-bacon-pasta-al-forno/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Allow the <strong>bacon &amp; cheese pasta</strong> to cool for a few minutes</p>\r\n<p>Serve with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
